flavor_text_entries.diamond:
Its impressive tusks are made of
ice. The population thinned when it
turned warm after the ice age.

flavor_text_entries.platinum:
A frozen one was dug up from
soil dating back 10,000 years. It
woke up to much amazement.
flavor_text_entries.heartgold:
A frozen MAMOSWINE was dug from ice
dating back 10,000 years. This Pokémon
has been around a long, long, long time.
flavor_text_entries.soulsilver:
It flourished worldwide during the
ice age but its population declined when
the masses of ice began to dwindle.

flavor_text_entries.sword:
This Pokémon can be spotted in wall paintings
from as far back as 10,000 years ago. For a
while, it was thought to have gone extinct.
flavor_text_entries.shield:
It looks strong, and that’s exactly what it is.
As the weather grows colder, its ice tusks
grow longer, thicker, and more impressive.
flavor_text_entries.legends-arceus:
This species reached its zenith during the period known as the
ice age. I suspect that Hisui's frigid climate is in harmony with
Mamoswine's constitution, thus awakening hidden potential.
